                Language
                ÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄ
        
        This  program can run in both Swedish and English. The program will
        check  your  country  setting  (COUNTRY  in  CONFIG.SYS)  and  will
        automatically set to Swedish if you live in Sweden, Norway, Denmark
        or  Finland, and otherwise to English. To override this setting you
        should  use the environment variable ANNLANG. It can have either of
        these two values:
        
            SWE    Swedish
            ENG    English
        
        You set it up with the command SET, for example:
        
            SET ANNLANG=ENG
        
        will  set  the language to English. If you want to set the language
        automatically when you start your computer, you can enter that line
        into your AUTOEXEC.BAT file.
        
